stylometry: The data mining method that we used was the cluster analysis. How I used it in my problem is; I first found a bunch of information (all the same 6 catagories) for every NBA team in the U.S. and then listed it all out. I then ran equations to standarize that data so that it made all the data be able to relate to all the other team's data. After that I ran searches to pull the information that had simularities in the clusters (groups of data) that I had gathered. Then I pulled out the top four teams that were the most simular in all the 6 catagories that I found data for all the teams in. I did all this beacause I wanted to see the top 4 teams that were the most simular in the stats of basketball that I was most interested in.
